<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="567" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2196</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Ambassador from Germany called about 11.40 and “expressed his
                                deep regret that the events of the war had led to the loss of the so
                                many American lives.”</p>
                            <p>Words in quotation marks in Ambassador’s writing.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>